<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7207> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7207" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Quaestor under Sertorius, 79, and proq. ?8 to 77 or 76? See MRR 2.80, 87, and 94. If the battles at Lauro in which he and his troops took part and defeated Pompey's legate, D. Laelius, took place in 77, the notice in MRR 2.94 should be placed under 77, Promagistrates (see below, on D. Laelius no. 5; Sall. Hist. 2.31M, from Schol. Bob. on Cic. Flacc. 14, p. 98St). It was then in the winter of 77/76 that Sertorius placed him in command against Metellus in Baetica (Liv. 91, fr. 22W). Or has the scholiast confused him with Herennius? See below, on Q. Hirtuleius (4).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4385> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4385" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably either Proquaestor or Legate under Sertorius when he fell in battle against Metellus Pius at Segovia (Sall. Hist. 2.59M; Liv. Per. 91; Frontin. Str. 2.3.5, and 7.5; Auct. Vir. Ill. 63.2; Oros. 5.23.12)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4349> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4349" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Sertorius in Spain. His troops shared in the victory over Pompey's Legate Laelius at Lauro (Sall. Hist. 2.31 M), but he was himself defeated and put to flight by Metellus at Italica (Oros. 5.23.10; cf. Frontin. Sir. 2.1.2, and 3.5). See 78, and 77, Promagistrates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4295> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4295" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served under Sertorius in Spain, probably with the title Proquaestor (see 79, Quaestors), where he defeated L. Manlius, Proconsul in Gaul, when he came to support Metellus in Spain (Liv. Per. 90; Frontin. Str. 1.5.8, Legatus; Plut. Sert. 12.4; Oros. 5.23.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/4263> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #4263" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Served in the government of Sertorius (Liv. Per. 90, quaestor, and 91; Plut. Sert. 12.3; see 80, note 6). Fortified Consabura on the Anas, and defeated and killed the Proconsul Domitius Calvinus (Liv. Per. 90; Plut. Sert. 12.3; Flor. 2.10.6; Eutrop. 6.1.2; Oros. 5.23.3; of. Frontin. 9tr. 4.5.19)." .
